 BY FOLASHADE KEHINDE PIONEER Vice Chancellor of the Lagos State University, Prof. Folabi Olumide, is dead. Olumide died on Friday, January 8, 2021, at the age of 81. Outgoing Vice Chancellor of LASU, Prof. Lanre Fagbohun, announced the late surgeon’s death, describing it as an irreplaceable loss. “Professor Olumide died today, Friday, 8th January, 2021, after a brief illness at the age of 81 years,” he said. Prof. Olumide served as LASU VC from inception in1983 to1988. Recall that the LASU Health Centre was, last year, renamed the Folabi Olumide Health Centre in his honour.  